    "recap_headline": "University of Louisiana at Lafayette Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LAFAYETTE \u2013\nJR Tollett\nand\nCody Brasch\ncombined on a four-hitter as Louisiana claimed its opening Sun Belt Conference series with a 3-1 victory over South Alabama on Sunday before an announced crowd of 3,507 at M. L. \"Tigue\" Moore Field at Russo Park.\nRigoberto Hernandez\ncollected two hits and drove in a pair of runs for Louisiana (15-5, 2-1 SBC), which allowed a first-inning run before shutting down South Alabama (13-7, 1-2 SBC) over the final eight innings.\nTollett (4-0) worked seven strong innings in his second quality start of the season for Louisiana, allowing three hits overall and one run in the opening frame. The right-hander walked two and struck out six in an 88-pitch effort. Brasch pitched the final two innings, giving up one hit and two walks while striking out three to record his third save of the season.\nSouth Alabama took an early lead in the first inning when Brennon Wright was hit by a pitch, stole second and scored on a base hit by Marc Stephens.\nLouisiana answered in the bottom of the inning against South Alabama starter Daniel Gonzalez (1-2).\nDonovan LaSalle\nwas hit by a pitch and later scored when\nDrew Markle\nlined a triple into the left-center field gap to tie the game. Hernandez followed with a one-out single to right field that plated Markle and gave the Cajuns a 2-1 lead.\nTollett worked out of trouble in the second inning after allowing the first two runners to reach base. He responded with a strikeout and a force out before making an athletic play on a bunt by Ethan Melton to end the threat.\nSouth Alabama mounted another challenge in the fifth when Melton singled with one out and Wright drew a walk. LaSalle preserved the lead with a diving catch on a wind-blown pop-up off the bat of Duncan Mathews and fired to first to complete the Cajuns' third double play of the game.\nTollett retired the side in order in both the sixth and seventh innings before handing the ball to Brasch.\nLouisiana added an insurance run in the fifth inning.\nNoah Lewis\ndrew a walk and moved to second after\nLee Amedee\nwas hit by a pitch following two strikeouts. Hernandez delivered again, lining an RBI single to extend the Cajuns' lead to 3-1.\nGonzales pitched five innings for South Alabama, allowing five hits and three runs. He walked two and struck out seven.\nThe victory capped a 3-1 week for Louisiana. The Cajuns travel Wednesday to face Big 12 opponent Houston at 6:30 p.m. before opening a weekend Sun Belt series against Texas State \u2013 the final weekend conference series between the schools \u2013 in San Marcos, Texas.\nFans are encouraged to stay engaged with the Ragin' Cajuns by downloading the #GeauxCajuns app. Click\nhere\nfor iOS/Apple platforms and\nhere\nfor Android platforms.\nFor the latest updates on Ragin' Cajuns baseball, follow on Facebook (RaginCajunsBaseball), Twitter (@RaginCajunsBSB) and Instagram (@RaginCajunsBSB) or check RaginCajuns.com."
  },
